-- Belgian Bankruptcies Rose 3% in First Half to 5,558, Tijd Says
-- B y   J e n n i f e r   M .   F r e e d m a n
-- 2012-07-03T06:04:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/belgian-bankruptcies-rose-3-in-first-half-to-5-558-tijd-says.html
A total of 5,558 Belgian companies
declared bankruptcy in the first half of 2012, up 3 percent from
a year earlier, De Tijd  reported , without saying where it got
the information.  In June alone, 990 Belgian businesses went bankrupt, the
worst figure for the month in recent decades, according to the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer M. Freedman in Geneva at 
